[CLAIM]
The authors reported that the more prospect’s frame was associated with risk, less were buyers willing to pay for that prospect: Framing a risky prospect as a “lottery ticket” (i.e., increased risk and uncertainty) reduced participants’ willingness to pay for the prospect, compared with to an uncertain “gift certificate” (i.e. reduced risk and uncertainty)

[HYPOTHESIS]
Participants in the lottery condition will have a lower mean willingness to pay than participants in the gift card condition. 
